00:32:59.330 --> 00:33:00.910
you couldn't use it, and
then you had to like go

00:33:00.910 --> 00:33:02.670
to the anthology and
see how it worked.

00:33:02.670 --> 00:33:04.220
Like why did you only
choose from the anthology?

00:33:04.220 --> 00:33:07.360
&gt;&gt; Eleanor Billington: Do you -- I
can answer that as well as Nealy.

00:33:07.360 --> 00:33:11.000
Nealy had to choose
from the anthology.

00:33:11.000 --> 00:33:13.150
The way this program works is
we have an anthology online

00:33:13.150 --> 00:33:14.980
of about 900 plus poems.

00:33:14.980 --> 00:33:17.470
And those are the poems that
the students can recite from.

00:33:17.470 --> 00:33:19.390
So those are the poems that
we've negotiated rights for,

00:33:19.390 --> 00:33:21.060
they're the ones that are
included in our anthology.

00:33:21.060 --> 00:33:22.850 position:56%
And so every summer, we update that.

00:33:22.850 --> 00:33:25.090
So we're always looking for
suggestions from anyone.

00:33:25.090 --> 00:33:27.840
Students can suggest poems,
teachers, the general public.

00:33:27.840 --> 00:33:29.990
So during the summer, we go
through the whole anthology,

00:33:29.990 --> 00:33:32.230
and we decide which
poems we're going to add,

00:33:32.230 --> 00:33:34.620
and how to negotiate rights for
that, and that kind of thing.

00:33:34.620 --> 00:33:35.940
So that's the way that it works.

00:33:35.940 --> 00:33:38.660
So if you guys have ideas and
if you want to email the NEA,

00:33:38.660 --> 00:33:41.950
me in particular, we
accept ideas all year long.

00:33:41.950 --> 00:33:44.020
And then we look at the poem over
the summer -- I mean, excuse me,

00:33:44.020 --> 00:33:46.870
we look at the anthology over the
summer to add, you know, new poems.

00:33:46.870 --> 00:33:50.430
So yes Nealy, Ahkei, Marta, they
had to choose from that anthology.

00:33:50.430 --> 00:33:52.490
Oftentimes, a student will
say, "I love this poem.

00:33:52.490 --> 00:33:53.790
Why is it not in there?"

00:33:53.790 --> 00:33:55.090
And they'll tell us
and we'll say, "Great,"

00:33:55.090 --> 00:33:56.390
and we try to add it that summer.

00:33:56.390 --> 00:33:57.690
So that's how it works.

00:33:57.690 --> 00:33:58.990
Yes, yes, of course.

00:33:58.990 --> 00:34:00.290
